Africa’s Largest Gold Producers Facing a Demand For 14% Increase in Wages

-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 
2011-06-12T08:45:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/africa-s-largest-gold-producers-facing-a-demand-for-14-increase-in-wages.html
South Africa ’s National Union of
Mineworkers said it begin wage talks with the Chamber of Mines
and will seek a wage increase of 14 percent.  “We are hopeful that the Chamber of Mines will accede to
our reasonable demands and that there will be no room for
confrontation,” NUM General Secretary Frans Baleni said in an
e-mailed statement today.  The Chamber of Mines represents gold companies including
 Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI) , Harmony Gold Mining Co. Ltd, and  AngloGold
Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  and collieries such as Anglocoal and Kangra, the
NUM said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  